Description: A zero-based index of the participants
A zero-based index of the conditions
The number of targets collected until (and including) this selection
The Nth selected target counting backwards from the last click in the patch
The total length of the item to item path that was created when foraging in the patch.
The distance between the previous and this target. NaN if there was no previous target or if this selection was not a target
The time between the previous and this target. NaN if there was no previous target or if this selection was not a target
The value of the selection. Defaults to 1
The spontaneous rate of return for this selection (value collected / time since last addition)
The spontaneous picking rate for this selection ( 1 / time since last element)
Whether or not (1 or 0) a switch occured since the last target selection. NaN if there was no previous target or if this selection was not a target
Value collected in this trial divided by the time spent in this trial
Number of targets selected in the trial
The length of the shortest path when taking the optimal trajectory through the patch.
The minimum Levenstein distance measure (evaluated for a set of grount truth sequences)
Measure of foraging organization. Best Kendall's tau for the selection sequence correlated with user-provided groundtruth orders.
Measure of foraging organization. Percentage points above the optimal path length.
Measure of foraging organization. Proportion of movements along a groundtruth pattern (in any direction) among all movements.
